<hl>
<seg id=1> Development of Chinese Mainland Economy Provides 5 Great Opportunities for HK SAR, Said Gu Yongjiang </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Gu Yongjiang said the development of mainland economy provided 5 opportunities for Hong Kong: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> -- beneficial to the long-term prosperity and stability of HK economy. </seg>
<seg id=4> HK economy will derive much benefit from the energetic mainland economy if it keeps a sustained and stable growth. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> -- Hong Kong meets more trade opportunities. </seg>
<seg id=6> As the inland service sectors are opened up step by step, such as trade, finance and retail, HK service sectors have a wider range of development. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> -- beneficial to Hong Kong's status as the trade and shipping hub. </seg>
<seg id=8> By the year 2010, mainland's international trade will go up to 800 billion US dollars, which will certainly increase the demand for transit and transship through Hong Kong, and thus benefits Hong Kong's status as the trade and shipping hub. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> -- Further promote the development of HK financial market. </seg>
<seg id=10> More and more joint-stock enterprises will be able to issue shares on markets outside the mainland as the deep going of state owned enterprises reforms. HK will be their first choice to issue shares,. </seg>
<seg id=11> As a result, HK stock scale will be enlarged, its stock market structure will be improved and HK security market will be enhanced with more Chinese funds emerging in HK. All the above will stable and build up Hong Kong's position as an international financial center. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> -- make Hong Kong's goods more competitive in international market. </seg>
<seg id=13> The mutual compensatory relation between mainland and Hong Kong economies enables the binding of the advantages of both sides, which can make Hong Kong products more competitive in international market. </seg>
</p>
